  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Teen Girls Health &amp; Empowerment in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda has the highest rate of teenage pregnancy in Sub-Saharan Africa. 50% of girls are married before they reach 18.   Shanti Uganda&apos;s Teen Girls Program uses education, prevention &amp; empowerment and has reached over 600 girls since 2010. With your help, we can reduce teen pregnancy, improve maternal health and keep girls in school.  Each girl makes her own reusable menstrual pad and learns about nutrition, reproductive health, HIV/AIDS, STIs, female role models and healthy relationships.</narrative>
  </description>
